In the typology of reputation, we can find some similar concepts such as direct reputation and indirect reputation but there are some slight semantic differences.
The FORe includes, as its kernel, the following concepts: reputation nature, roles involved in reputation formation and propagation, information sources for reputation, evaluation of reputation, and reputation maintenance.
For instance, Image and Reputation are two central concepts in the cognitive reputation model.
The Functional Ontology of Reputation (FORe) was defined as a common semantic basis that subsumes the concepts of the main reputation models.
The ontology concept ReputationNature is composed of concepts such as IndividualReputation 